Profile?language=EN>Northerner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 3:54:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22899.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.shaw.ca/sjgardner/Images/celeris2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Religion is not masked whatsoever by player Illusions.  Enchanters (including myself at the time) were more than a little miffed to find this out years ago and griped rather loudly about it.  If was left unchanged.<br><br>I've always felt it a little odd that Verant was dissapointed in the number of players that chose the Agnostic route when they consistantly placed barriers in front of those players that chose a religion.  Heck, I even went Agnostic myself at a time when worshipping Bristlebane might have unforseen consequences.  At present though, it generally is not a faction problem.  Those who worship obviously good or evil deities may well have problems even when using illusions though. <p><center><b><font color=RED><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78504>Celeris Tujimson</a><br>Blackguard of The Nameless<br></font></b><font color=CYAN size=2><i>"The church is near but the road is icy; the bar is far away but I'll walk carefully." ~Russian Proverb</i> </font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulannellavelglarn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lannella Velglarn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/lannella/leaf.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 4:17:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22899.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/housecalls/nextlevel.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just a silly question involving masks/illusions...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Also why don’t we get any masks like Goblin or Kobold? Is there a reason or do you think they someday they may be added?&quot;<br><br>One reason is that, as I understand, for each illusion mask or spell out there, VI must add that Race to each and every zone's mob list, so every zone would have to have Goblin and Kobold, etc in its files.  Thus, I believe, they are hesitant to put to many out there. <p><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111" width="100%" id="AutoNumber1" bgcolor="#FFFFFF">  <tr>    <td width="100%"><font face="Verdana"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6443">    <font color="#FF0000">LANNELLA VELG'LARN</font></A><font color="#FF0000">, <</font><A   href="http://www.rutabaga-paradox.com/"><font color="#FF0000">Rutabaga Paradox</font></A><font color="#FF0000">></font><FONT size=1><RUTABAGA   Paradox></rutabaga></FONT><font color="#FF0000">, Druzzil Ro<br>    </DIV></font><A href="http://come.to/TheHighway">    <font color="#FF0000">Nindolen</font><font color="#FF0000">   d'Colbauth</font></A><font color="#FF0000"> (</font><A href="http://come.to/TheHighway"><EM><font color="#FF0000">Thief of   the Highway</font></EM></A><font color="#FF0000">) <EM><STRONG> 52    <br>    "</STRONG></EM></font><A   href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouselibraryreadonly.showMessage?topicID=98.topic"><EM><STRONG><font color="#FF0000">Rogueling</font></STRONG></EM></A><EM><font color="#FF0000"><STRONG>?      Go.  Take this note and ask for </STRONG></font><A href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showMessage?topicID=12393.topic">    <STRONG><font color="#FF0000">counsel</font></STRONG></A><font color="#FF0000"><STRONG>."</STRONG></font></EM><font color="#FF0000"><b>    <br>    <font size="1">(The preceding links brought to you by the letters F, A, & Q)</font></b></font></font></td>  </tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uinkiewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inkiewiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/19/02 4:20:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22899.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.strike9.com/eq/file.aspx/path=/inkiewiz/fullsize/iriasmall3.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> Well, in a roleplaying sense ... if you were trying to blend into a certain group, you'd stick out unless you had done significant research.  You wouldn't know the catch-phrases, ritual gestures, community no-nos, etc.  The more restrictive the group (religious fanatics, for example), the more true this is.<br><br>And actually, this is kind of how it is in EQ.  As a half-elf, with my DE mask, I can safely wander around the public spaces of Oggok (guards and merchants are apprehensive to me with mask). But I don't go into, for example, the SK or shaman guilds, which are likely to be a more religious, more restrictive (read: would like to tear my throat out) group of people.<br><br>I'm kind of curious how well the Iksar mask works, given that all Iksar worship Cazic Thule. As far as I remember, rogues and bards can't worship CT.  Maybe human rogues/bards, dunno.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.show